  plugins: [react()],
});
```

By using the `import` syntax instead of `require`, you're telling Node.js to treat the file as an ECMAScript Module, which is the recommended way to import the Vite API.

If you're still encountering issues after making this change, you can try clearing your Node.js cache by running `npm cache clean --force` or `yarn cache clean` before running Vite again.

Additionally, make sure you're using a recent version of Node.js that supports ECMAScript Modules. Node.js 14.x and later versions have stable support for ECMAScript Modules.

