Ah, I see the issue now. The error is related to the `value` prop of the `Select` component. The `Select` component expects the `value` prop to be of type `string | null`, but you're passing a string value (`projectName`) that can potentially be an empty string (`""`).

To fix this error, you can use a type guard or a conditional check to ensure that the `value` prop is either a non-empty string or `null`.

Here's an example of how you can modify your code to resolve the error:

```jsx
<Select
  id="select-projectName"
  value={projectName || null} // Use null if projectName is an empty string
  label="Select project"
  onChange={handleChange}
  fullWidth={true}
>
  <MenuItem value="">All projects</MenuItem>
  <MenuItem value="user">My projects</MenuItem>
  {testData.projectNames.sort().map((project) => (
    <MenuItem value={project} key={project}>
      {project}
    </MenuItem>
  ))}
</Select>
```

In this updated code:

1. We're using the logical OR operator (`||`) to pass either the `projectName` value or `null` to the `value` prop of the `Select` component. If `projectName` is an empty string (`""`), it will be treated as a falsy value, and `null` will be assigned to the `value` prop.
2. We've added a `MenuItem` with an empty string value (`value=""`) to represent the "All projects" option.

By making these changes, the `Select` component will receive a valid value (`string | null`) for the `value` prop, and the TypeScript error should be resolved.

